        "title": "revert: retire API key required skill feature",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- remove the API-key-required evaluator, publish-time scheduling, write paths, public API/search exposure, and UI badges introduced by #2353\n- add a temporary no-op drain for already-scheduled evaluator jobs\n- add a bounded, resumable, confirmation-gated cleanup for legacy `apiKeyRequired` fields in `skillVersions`, `skills.latestVersionSummary`, and `skillSearchDigest`\n- retain the three optional schema fields only until production cleanup is verified; a follow-up will remove those fields plus the temporary migration/state/drain\n\n## Rollout\n\n1. Merge and deploy this removal so no new values are written and queued legacy jobs drain harmlessly.\n2. Take a manual Convex production backup.\n3. Run and review the bounded production dry run.\n4. Explicitly approve and apply the cleanup until complete, then verify a second dry run reports zero matches.\n5. Remove the temporary cleanup function/state table, compatibility schema fields, and queued-job drain in a follow-up PR.\n\n## Proof\n\n- Autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Real local Convex/browser proof is blocked before these functions deploy by an unrelated stale local fixture: a `packageReleases` document still contains removed field `clawScanNote`. That fixture was intentionally left untouched.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `bunx vitest run convex/removeApiKeyRequiredData.test.ts convex/llmEval.test.ts convex/lib/skillPublish.test.ts`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit` (264 passed, 1 skipped files; 3130 passed, 1 skipped tests)\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `bunx convex dev --once --typecheck=disable` (blocked by the unrelated stale local `packageReleases.clawScanNote` fixture noted above)\n",
